Today's lesson topic is "Diagonal Lines Power".
You may have read from basic tactics article, about the use of lines,
Can you count, how many places here can give black at least one active pair?
i go again, line by line
So, mathematically, we get same resuly,
from both vertical and diagonal lines,
but practically the situation is different:
diagonal line's 21 points are located in larger space
which give black much more opportunities to develop
vertical line's points were concentrated tightly around the main line
Which means, by some simple block, white can defend easily.
Suppose white could make 3 defense stones now,
Indeed, white can defend against the power horizontal line.
black  has very powerful attacks here:)
Can white defend here with 3 stones??
No matter how we defend, we will end up with d4 opening somehow,
So, as you see, although we realized that mathematically black has same chances of making lines,
the diagonal lines are more powerful especially because white is not able to block the diagonal power.
That makes i7 and d4 openings strong - it develops strongly along the diagonal.
White's first choice is to block diagnal line??
So, remember, when you have a choice in development, then choose diagonal development, because of its larger space potential.
Yes, when you are in defense, then block the diagonal line instead of horizontal.
Of course there are exceptions, but mostly it works this way.
i think there are some exeprions )))
The fans of net defense make a classical mistake -
Assuming it takes a key point
the last one perhaps the strongest
White believed the net defense is the best,
but actually to control diagonal line is usually more important.

The first idea of diagonal line:
to gain more space around the pair.
my   engish  can  make  a  great  prograss  ,too

so it would make white worry about increasing space for black.
the third meaning is: to activate the supporting lines,
the diagonal pair 17_23 is effectively using the Inner Structures,
And now the space is big enough to carry out a very powerful attack.

It is the diagonal line with one or more empty spots in it.
